<TITLE> Seaports hoist signal 3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com) The deep monsoon depression in the northwest and surrounding areas in the Bay moving slightly northwestward was crossing the Orissa coasts over Puri in India at 9am Friday, met office said. Within 48 km of the centre of the depression, sustained wind speed is about 50-60 kph. Gusty to squally winds may blow over the seaports under the influence of the depression. Chittagong, Mongla and Cox's Bazar seaports have been advised to hoist local cautionary signal three until further notice. The fishing boats and trawlers have been advised not to venture out into the sea until otherwise notified. The coastal districts of Noakhali, Laxmipur, Bhola, Patuakhali, Barisal, Chandpur, Barguna, Pirojpur, Jhalokathhi, Bagerhat, Khulna, Satkhira and the offshore shoals are likely to experience wind-driven surge two to four feet higher than the regular tide. bdnew
